cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with machine translation tasks and language generation. It could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it involves the use of transformer models and attention mechanisms. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it involves the use of neural networks for translation tasks. Finally, it could also be categorized under cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) as it involves the use of back-translation for data augmentation, which is a common technique in computer vision tasks.
